  "prompt": "Are shares debt or equity?",
  "response": "Shares are equity, not debt. When a company issues shares, it is selling a portion of ownership in the company to shareholders. Unlike debt, which represents a loan that must be repaid with interest, shares represent:\n\n1. Partial ownership in the company\n2. A claim on the company's assets and earnings\n3. Potential voting rights in company decisions\n4. Possible dividend payments, but not guaranteed\n\nShareholders are considered part-owners of the company and can potentially benefit from the company's growth, but they also take on the risk of potential losses if the company performs poorly.",
